<HEADLINE>
QUESTIONS, QUESTIONS, QUESTIONS 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 (With TV-XFILES)   
 c.1999 Seattle Post-Intelligencer  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Fox's commercials for episodes airing Sunday and Feb. 14
promise: ``The `X-Files' conspiracy exposed!'' Well, yes and no.
Here's a glance at mysteries that are solved, and some loose ends.
</P>
<P>
   Answered
</P>
<P>
   _ What is the Cigarette Smoking Man's name?
</P>
<P>
   _ What is his part in the Syndicate, and in the Syndicate's
conspiracy with aliens?
</P>
<P>
   _ What is the reason for the conspiracy?
</P>
<P>
   _ Whose side is Agent Spender on?
</P>
<P>
   _ What is the significance of the black oil?
</P>
<P>
   Not Answered
</P>
<P>
   _ Who is Fox Mulder's father?
</P>
<P>
   _ What is Agent Diana Fowley's connection to Mulder?
</P>
<P>
   _ What is the significance of Gibson Praise, the clairvoyant
child?
</P>
<P>
   _ Where is Mulder's sister, Samantha?
</P>
<P>
   _ What's up with Krycek?
</P>
</TEXT>
