<DATE_TIME> 1999-02-06 01:39 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A4333 &Cx1f; ttc-z
r s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-BKN-LAKERS-ROCKETS-LA     02-06 0675
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKN-LAKERS-ROCKETS-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
LAKERS BEAT ROCKETS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By HOWARD BECK  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   INGLEWOOD, Calif. _ When at last the extended offseason of woe
ended, and the NBA turned away from its labor war and the end of
the Michael Jordan era, it figured to be a while, perhaps years,
before the league's future would come into focus under a new star.
</P>
<P>
   But impatient Kobe Bryant didn't wait for his cue.
</P>
<P>
   As if the constellations had aligned in Bryant's favor, the Los
Angeles Lakers lost their two top small forwards to unusual
circumstances Friday, and Bryant stepped into the starting lineup _
for his first career opening-night start. Against the collection of
legends known as the Houston Rockets. Against Scottie Pippen.
</P>
<P>
   And Bryant being Bryant, he wasted no time asserting himself. He
scored seven points in the first quarter, outplayed Pippen the
entire game and finished with his first career double-double, 25
points and 10 rebounds, as the Lakers held off the Rockets 99-91 at
the Forum.
</P>
<P>
   Shaquille O'Neal started slowly but finished with a team-high 30
points and 14 rebounds. Charles Barkley had 31 points and 15
rebounds to lead Houston.
</P>
<P>
   Bryant not only powered the Lakers offense, he shut down Pippen,
holding him to 10 points on 4-of-18 shooting.
</P>
<P>
   Not a bad night for the Lakers' third option at small forward.
</P>
<P>
   Coach Del Harris intends to use Bryant off the bench again this
season, but he had no choice Friday. Starter Rick Fox is hampered
by sore ankles and knees and can't play again until his new
athletic insoles arrive, possibly not until Tuesday. Robert Horry,
Harris' next preferred option, was in Houston with his wife and
newborn son.
</P>
<P>
   But Harris wasn't worried about thrusting the 20-year-old Bryant
into the lineup, no matter the opponent.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's experienced quite a lot already,'' Harris said before
tipoff. ``The guy's started the All-Star Game and played key roles
in playoff series.... I think he can handle it.''
</P>
<P>
   So well, in fact, that Bryant could make a case to play Lou
Gehrig to Fox's Wally Pip. Harris has said he didn't want to start
Bryant until he was ready to be the starter for the rest of his
career.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's possible,'' he said of leaving Bryant in the lineup
permanently. ``Normally we let (an injured starter) come back and
start at that position until they are knocked out of the position.
I assume that's what we'll do here as well.
</P>
<P>
   ``Ideally, when Kobe Bryant obviously establishes himself as a
guy that you just can't keep out of the starting lineup, you put
him there, and he'll stay in there for the next 10 or 12 years.
That's what you would hope for, and that could happen at any
time.''
</P>
<P>
   Maybe it already has. Fox is likely to miss Sunday's game as
well, and Harris will have to decide whether to start Horry at
power forward, his usual spot, or small forward.
</P>
<P>
   If Bryant was nervous about starting opening night, he certainly
lied well.
</P>
<P>
   ``I feel very calm,'' he said before the game. ``It's kind of
like a new feeling for me; usually in the past I've just been,
whew, rush of adrenaline, you know what I mean? I'm very, very
excited, but I learned very quickly about how to play the game
emotionally. I'm surprisingly calm. I didn't really expect to be
calm. Period, coming out for opening night, let alone starting.''
</P>
<P>
   Playing against Bulls alum Pippen, he of the six championship
rings, Bryant called it ``a chance to learn'' from Jordan's old
running mate. Turns out Bryant was the master this night.
</P>
<P>
   Notes: Horry's wife Keva gave birth to their second child,
Robert Camron Horry, at 5 p.m. CST. He weighs 8 pounds, 11 ounces,
and both mother and baby were said to be doing fine.... Barkley was
wearing a pair of Air Jordans, with Michael's No. 23 imprinted on
the heels. ``Nike said they wanted other players to wear Michael's
shoes as a tribute to him,'' Barkley said, ``but I know better.
They just wanted the other guys to sell his shoes for him.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
