six years after an El Al plane crashed into a low-income housing
complex in Amsterdam and killed 43 people, emotions run high over
speculation that the cargo held nerve gas agents for use by
Israel's military. By Marlise Simons.
</P>
<P>
   EXP-IMPEACH-TRIAL (Washington) _ Senators on Saturday watched
excerpts from the videotaped depositions of Monica Lewinsky, Vernon
Jordan and Sidney Blumenthal, in the final session of the
evidentiary stage of the trial of the president. By David E.
Rosenbaum.
</P>
<P>
   EXP-IMPEACH-LEADERS (Washington) _ Amid the partisan fires of
the impeachment and trial of President Clinton, the Senate majority
leader, Trent Lott of Mississippi, and the minority leader, Tom
Daschle of South Dakota, managed to forge a better relationship
than they had ever had before. ``Both senators like each other,''
one of their colleagues said, citing that as one reason that ``the
Senate didn't spin out of control.'' By Frank Bruni.
</P>
<P>
   EXP-IMPEACH-ROGAN (Washington) _ As one of the 13 House
prosecutors, James E. Rogan, 41, has greater name recognition in
his second term than many of his colleagues do after decades in
office. But it is this starring role that has put Mr. Rogan on the
Democratic Party's short list of Republicans from moderate
districts who are most likely to suffer a voter backlash in 2000.
By Evelyn Nieves.
</P>
<P>
   EXP-DRAFT-REVIVAL-REVIEW (Washington) _ A quarter century after
the last conscripts mustered at boot camp, the idea of reviving the
draft has gained new currency among a small lot of academics,
lawmakers and, even, military commanders. By Steven Lee Myers.
</P>
<P>
   EXP-EX-SPIES-REVIEW (Undated) _ Hundreds of former CIA and KGB
agents are working together as business partners to provide
sensitive information to American corporations. By Leslie Wayne.
</P>
<P>
   EXP-SNOWMOBILE-BAN (Grand Lake, Colo.) _ The coalition called
the Bluewater Network,has petitioned Interior Secretary Bruce
Babbitt to ban snowmobiles from the 28 places among the National
Park System's 378 that allow them. By James Brooke.
</P>
<P>
   EXP-FAMILY-TREES (New York) _ With many families of the 1990s no
longer fitting the nuclear family model of the 1950s, teachers are
rearranging lesson plans and redrawing assignments long regarded as
staples of the classroom. By Lynette Holloway.
</P>
<P>
   EXP-PRESERVING-DOCUMENTS (Washington) _ This week, the National
Archives and Records Administration is expected to unveil the
design of the new enclosures for the Declaration of Independence,
Constitution and Bill of Rights. By Warren E. Leary.
</P>
<P>
   EXP-SOFTWARE-LAWYER (Houston) _ In a ruling last month thought
to be the first of its type in the country, Judge Barefoot Sanders
of Federal District Court in Dallas found that Parsons Technology
Inc., which publishes Quicken Family Lawyer and Quicken Family
Lawyer '99, goes too far in the assistance it provides consumers,
resulting in an unauthorized practice of law in the state. By
Barbara Whitaker.
</P>
