   GOVERNORS-REVERSE (Sacramento) _ Gray Davis won the California
governor's race by using the Clinton playbook: deliver a centrist
message offering to use ideas from both sides of the aisle. But the
first weeks of his term have been spent undoing the work of his
Republican predecessor, Pete Wilson. By Terri Hardy. (Will move on
