   IMPEACH-TRIAL (Washington) _ With the end of President Clinton's
impeachment trial in sight, House prosecutors on Saturday showed
the Senate videotaped excerpts from the sworn depositions of Monica
Lewinsky _ the first time the public had a chance to see her speak
since her affair with the president became known a year ago.
Prosecutors clearly hoped that the senators and the public would be
struck by Ms. Lewinsky's youth and vulnerability and that this
impression would work to Clinton's disadvantage. By David E.
Rosenbaum.
