and a shorter version at 2150 words. The obituary carried an ``a''
general news category code; other stories will use an ``i''
international category code. At the appropriate time, we will
re-top the obituary and release it. Until official notification is
released, these are the stories planned for Sunday:
</P>
<P>
   JORDAN-HUSSEIN (Amman, Jordan) _ With King Hussein unconscious
and near death, Jordan's government transferred full powers
Saturday to Crown Prince Abdullah, making the 37-year-old heir to
the throne king in all but name and effectively ending Hussein's
rule after 47 years. By Douglas Jehl.
</P>
<P>
   JORDAN-PRINCE (Amman, Jordan) _ As Crown Prince Abdullah
formally took charge of Jordan's government Saturday, experienced
observers here said that internal political challenges _ rather
than foreign affairs crises _ are likely to present the new king
with his first leadership tests. By William A. Orme Jr.
</P>
