for Sunday.    (The ``HNS'' tag appears in all sluglines.)   
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON NEWS (``w'' category)
</P>
<P>
   IMPEACH-TRIAL (Washington) _ There were no ``Perry Mason
moments'' in the closing arugments at President Clinton's
impeachment trial Saturday. But the president and Monica Lewinsky
and other witnesses were vividly portrayed on four TV monitors in
the Senate chamber as the prosecution and defense went to the
videotape to find evidence to convict or acquit Clinton. By DAN
FREEDMAN.
</P>
