<P>
   JORDAN-HUSSEIN-0207 _ AMMAN, Jordan _ As the hour-by-hour vigil
over the gravely ill body of this country's monarch continued for a
second day, a profound question has arisen: How does Islamic law _
one of the most strict of all religions _ deal with removing
someone from life support? Although the family of Jordan's King
Hussein decided late Friday night to leave him on life support _
for now _ it did not come without some reportedly heated debate
among those members. Developing. (Kaplow, Cox News Service)
</P>
<P>
   REFUGEE-SMUGGLING _ MIAMI _ They used to come on oil drums,
inner-tubes, or anything else remotely resembling a raft. Now they
come in speedboats piloted by dearly paid smugglers. Hundreds of
illegal immigrants have come ashore in South Florida in recent
weeks. And, overall, there's been a 400 percent increase in illegal
immigrants nabbed on Florida shores over the past year. Most of the
immigrants are coming from Cuba and Haiti. Experts say the dramatic
jump in illegal immigration _ if not stopped _ could further
overcrowd U.S. schools and strain government services. (Emling, Cox
News Service)
</P>
<P>
   w/REFUGEE-DATA _ MIAMI _ Numbers for a box and information for a
map showing routes taken by refugee groups. (Emling, Cox News
Service).
</P>
