<P>
   HKN-BOUCHARD _ Former Atlanta Flames standout Dan Bouchard was
in goal when the Ice Age arrived in Atlanta and then when it melted
away eight years later in 1980. Now, as the NHL prepares to return
to Atlanta, Bouchard is back in the game. Bouchard, who underwent
brain surgery in 1990, is coach of Life University, which is going
for its third straight national title in ice hockey. Life, whose
roster is filled with Canadians, competes in the National
Collegiate Hockey Association's Division II. Bouchard helped form
the club team four years ago. (Curtright, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 25. WTH PHOTOS. MOVED
