<P>
   JAMES-DREAM (Untitled) _ In December, when Jesse Tonks entered a
dream-trip contest titled ``Places to Remember,'' sponsored by the
London Daily Express, which is nationally distributed in Britain.
Tonks' entry letter so intrigued the Express editors that they
plucked him from Midlands obscurity, declared him a winner and
quickly made arrangements to send him to the heart of Jesse James
country: Kansas City and St. Joseph. Two takes. By JOE POPPER. Will
move in ``a'' category. &QL;
