<P>
   (NYT12) ATLANTA -- Feb. 6, 1999 -- SOCSEC-DEBATE, 2-6 -- For
today's aging baby boomers, who face concerns about the solvency of
Social Security and other federal retirement programs, it is now
the government that cannot be trusted and a bullish Wall Street
that provides hope. ``I can't see the federal government being a
player in the stock market,'' says Kevin S. Green, left, 36, a
lawyer.'' Rod D. Jackson, right, 38, a maintenance man says, ``A
lot of people don't have knowledge of how the stock market works
and could lose a lot of money.'' (Alan S. Weiner/New York Times
Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT11) POUND RIDGE, N.Y. -- Feb. 6, 1999 -- DOGSHOW-PREPARE,
2-6 -- Casey, a golden retriever who is almost 6 years old, with
Lisa Smith his owner and trainer during a treadmill workout. Casey
is among 2,500 entrants competing on Monday and Tuesday at Madison
Square Garden in the 123d annual Westminster Kennel Club Dog Show,
