<P>
   &QL; 
CHIROPRACTOR (undated) _ Petite and 50ish, she crosses her arms
over her chest as if to protect herself from a body blow. Then her
doctor stands over her and then leans into her, his hand shoving
her shoulder like a stuck door. That done, he moves up to her head,
runs his fingers matter-of-factly down her neck. He putshis hand at
the base of her skull; places the other hand on her forehead and
then twists her head like a balky pickle-jar lid. Depending on what
you believe, what just happened to Alicefayehall Orban with her
chiropractor, Dr. Edwin Weathersby, was either health care or
hocus-pocus. By JODIE SNYDER. Story will move in the ``A''
category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
BASKETBALL (Scottsdale, Ariz.) _ Driving up Scottsdale Road one
Saturday morning, DanWelton spotted a couple of guys shooting hoops
at Cactus Park. The next week, he showed up in high tops for a
pick-up game. That was five years ago. The game grew into a weekly
ritual for the 39-year-old Honeywell facilities analyst and about
12 other guys. They know whatever the weather, come 7:30 on
Saturday mornings, the guys will be there for a game of
four-on-four, simply for the love of basketball. By LAURA TRUJILLO.
Story will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
